body:
1. Name your placeholders... then it is clear where they are defined

i.e. tf.placeholder(name="something I know about")

2. It tells you in the 2nd traceback where the placeholder that is unspecified:

```
Caused by op u'Placeholder_9', defined at:
...
  File "<ipython-input-73-76942abbcce5>", line 45, in create_Q_network
    self.state_input = tf.placeholder("float",[None,self.state_dim])
```

3. It tells you what sess.run() call failed to have all the placeholders in the traceback too.

```
<ipython-input-98-ea92c0cb6f5e> in train_Q_network(self)
    105         summary_str = self.session.run(merged_summary_op,feed_dict={
    106                 self.y_input : y_batch,
--> 107                 self.action_input : action_batch,
    108                 **#self.state_input : state_batch**
    109                 })    
```
Notice how self.state_input feed is commented out.

4. This question is not a bug with TensorFlow so is more appropriate for StackOverflow. So I am closing for now.
